        <mxCell id="Xc2n890nvd468IkJG_eE-0" value="&lt;h1&gt;Opportunities for Hub as a Product ( with this approach )&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. Enterprises can share the Hub Keys and Hub wallet secrets ( Secret 2 ) with 3rd Parties. As a result, original wallet keys need not to be shared with third parties.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. Hub can develop a time limited wallet share feature. With this feature, the enterprises can create a time bounded Hub wallet secretes ( another Pair of Secret 1 and Secret 2 ) and new Secret 2 can be shared with any other 3rd Party.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As the above Secret 2 is time bounded, Enterprises need not to worry about maintaining a list of Trusted 3rd Parties. Additionaly, the Hub can provide a revoke feature for any time bounded Secrets. Revoking time bounded secret will delete the encrypted copy of the wallet keys.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. As Hub cannot see the wallet keys without having the secrets, it is Custodian to the Hub User.&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="H--bJcAQ3lL-xQJmQ7f_-1">
